---
export const prerender = true;
import LightLayout from '../layouts/LightLayout.astro';
import { ICON_PATHS } from '../data/icons';
import { EXPOSE_CASE_STUDIES } from '../data/exposeCaseStudies';
---

<LightLayout title="Expose — Choose Your Tool">
  <main class="relative z-10 max-w-[1100px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 bg-retro-bg">

    <div class="mb-8 text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-[0.22em] flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-retro-ink transition">Lattice</a>
      <span class="text-retro-ink/20">/</span>
      <span class="text-retro-ink">Expose</span>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-retro-ink/15 pt-3 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between text-[9px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-[0.22em] mb-10">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 sm:gap-5">
        <span>EXPOSE · v0.3</span>
        <span class="hidden md:inline">Choose how you want to follow people, money, and organisations</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-retro-green"></span>
        <span>Public beta</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <header class="mb-16">
      <div class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-green uppercase tracking-[0.22em] mb-3">A Lattice product</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-semibold text-retro-ink tracking-tight leading-[1.05] mb-5">
        Expose <span class="italic font-light text-retro-green">— pick the interface that fits the job.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-retro-slate leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        Expose can work while you read or answer direct questions. Use the browser extension when you want context to appear inside articles, or use the chatbot when you want to ask direct questions and follow a thread across people, organisations, ownership, funding, and public records.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <article class="bg-white border border-retro-border rounded-md p-6 lg:p-8 shadow-[4px_4px_0px_rgba(230,230,230,1)] border-t-4 border-t-retro-green">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 mb-6">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-11 h-11 rounded-sm border border-retro-green/30 bg-retro-green/5 flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-retro-green" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" set:html={ICON_PATHS.search} />
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-widest">Option 01</p>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-retro-ink tracking-tight">Browser extension</h2>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-green uppercase tracking-widest">Best while reading</span>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-retro-slate leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Underlines names inside articles and pages, then shows quick context on hover and a fuller dossier on click. Best when you want context without leaving the page.
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-retro-ink mb-8">
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-retro-green font-mono text-xs mt-1">✓</span><span>Works while you browse news, company pages, and public filings</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-retro-green font-mono text-xs mt-1">✓</span><span>Highlights politicians, companies, think tanks, and media brands</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-retro-green font-mono text-xs mt-1">✓</span><span>Shows ownership, funding, and source-linked context inline</span></li>
          </ul>

          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
            <a href="#extension-install" class="inline-block text-center bg-retro-green text-white px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-retro-ledger transition-colors rounded-sm shadow-[3px_3px_0px_rgba(15,61,46,1)] hover:shadow-none hover:translate-x-[3px] hover:translate-y-[3px]">
              Choose extension →
            </a>
            <a href="https://github.com/annamariawettstein/remove-barriers/tree/annamariawettstein/copy-repo-aesthetic/extension" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-block text-center text-retro-ink border border-retro-ink bg-white px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-retro-bg transition rounded-sm">
              View source →
            </a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="bg-retro-ink text-white rounded-md p-6 lg:p-8 shadow-[6px_6px_0px_rgba(15,61,46,0.95)]">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 mb-6">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-11 h-11 rounded-sm border border-white/15 bg-white/5 flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-white" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" set:html={ICON_PATHS.speech} />
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50 uppercase tracking-widest">Option 02</p>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">3D investigator</h2>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-green uppercase tracking-widest">Best for questions</span>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Search for a person or company and open the 3D Expose tool from the `Data Weaver 3D` codebase. Best when you want to investigate a topic directly instead of waiting to spot it in an article.
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-white/90 mb-8">
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-retro-green font-mono text-xs mt-1">✓</span><span>Interactive 3D graph view for names, companies, and reported links</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-retro-green font-mono text-xs mt-1">✓</span><span>Plain-English summary under the graph once research loads</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-retro-green font-mono text-xs mt-1">✓</span><span>Source verification and fallback search links for weak citations</span></li>
          </ul>

          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
            <a href="/expose-tool" class="inline-block text-center bg-white text-retro-ink px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-retro-bg transition-colors rounded-sm">
              Open 3D tool →
            </a>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center text-[10px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase tracking-widest px-3 py-3 border border-white/10 rounded-sm">
              Same data, different interface
            </span>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-[0.22em] mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-retro-green" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" set:html={ICON_PATHS.summary} />
        Which one should I use?
      </h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        <div class="bg-white border border-retro-border rounded-md p-6">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl text-retro-green mb-4 border border-retro-green/30 bg-retro-green/5 w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm">01</div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-retro-ink mb-2">Use the extension when</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-retro-slate leading-relaxed">You are already reading an article and want context to appear around the names on the page.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-retro-border rounded-md p-6">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl text-retro-green mb-4 border border-retro-green/30 bg-retro-green/5 w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm">02</div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-retro-ink mb-2">Use the chatbot when</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-retro-slate leading-relaxed">You already know what you want to ask and want an answer in plain English with the thread pulled together for you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-retro-border rounded-md p-6">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl text-retro-green mb-4 border border-retro-green/30 bg-retro-green/5 w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center rounded-sm">03</div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-retro-ink mb-2">Use both when</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-retro-slate leading-relaxed">You spot a name in an article, then want to go deeper and ask follow-up questions across the wider network.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-end justify-between gap-4 mb-6">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <h2 class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-[0.22em] mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-retro-green" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" set:html={ICON_PATHS.graph} />
            Case studies
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-retro-slate leading-relaxed">
            Start with real UK influence cases that show how hidden networks usually work in practice: social brokers, elite schools, revolving doors, institutional protection, and media-political dependency.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-[0.22em]">
          {String(EXPOSE_CASE_STUDIES.length).padStart(2, '0')} network studies
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {EXPOSE_CASE_STUDIES.map((study, index) => (
          <article class="bg-white border border-retro-border rounded-md p-6 lg:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-4">
              <div>
                <p class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-green uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Case {String(index + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</p>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-retro-ink tracking-tight">{study.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-retro-slate mt-1">{study.subtitle}</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <p class="text-sm text-retro-ink leading-relaxed mb-5">{study.summary}</p>

            <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-[9px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Hidden pattern</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-retro-slate leading-relaxed">{study.hiddenPattern}</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-[9px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Why it matters</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-retro-slate leading-relaxed">{study.whyItMatters}</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-5">
              <a
                href={`/expose-tool?name=${encodeURIComponent(study.primaryQuery)}`}
                class="inline-block bg-retro-green text-white px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-retro-ledger transition-colors rounded-sm shadow-[3px_3px_0px_rgba(15,61,46,1)] hover:shadow-none hover:translate-x-[3px] hover:translate-y-[3px]"
              >
                Start with {study.primaryQuery} →
              </a>
              {study.supportingQueries.slice(0, 2).map((query) => (
                <a
                  href={`/expose-tool?name=${encodeURIComponent(query)}`}
                  class="inline-block border border-retro-border bg-retro-bg px-4 py-2 text-sm text-retro-ink hover:bg-white transition rounded-sm"
                >
                  {query}
                </a>
              ))}
            </div>

            <p class="text-[11px] text-retro-slate italic">Use these as research entry points, then follow the wider network from the graph and the source cards below it.</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-20" id="extension-install">
      <h2 class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-[0.22em] mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-retro-green" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" set:html={ICON_PATHS.check} />
        Browser extension install
      </h2>
      <div class="bg-white border border-retro-border rounded-md p-6 lg:p-8">
        <div class="text-[10px] font-mono text-retro-green uppercase tracking-[0.22em] mb-3">Beta · load as unpacked extension</div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-retro-ink tracking-tight mb-4">Five steps in Chrome, Edge, or Brave</h3>
        <ol class="space-y-3 text-sm text-retro-ink max-w-2xl mb-6">
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="font-mono text-retro-green text-xs mt-1">01</span><span>Download the <code class="text-retro-ink bg-retro-bg px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-sm">extension/</code> folder from the repo</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="font-mono text-retro-green text-xs mt-1">02</span><span>Open <code class="text-retro-ink bg-retro-bg px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-sm">chrome://extensions</code></span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="font-mono text-retro-green text-xs mt-1">03</span><span>Turn on <strong>Developer mode</strong></span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="font-mono text-retro-green text-xs mt-1">04</span><span>Click <strong>Load unpacked</strong> and choose the <code class="text-retro-ink bg-retro-bg px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-sm">extension/</code> folder</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="font-mono text-retro-green text-xs mt-1">05</span><span>Pin it to the toolbar and visit a page with people or organisation names in the text</span></li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-[11px] text-retro-slate italic">The current beta uses a seeded public-data set for UK politicians, parties, think tanks, companies, ownership structures, and media brands.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="mt-16 pt-6 border-t border-retro-ink/15 flex flex-col gap-2 md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between text-[9px] font-mono text-retro-slate uppercase tracking-[0.22em]">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <span>Expose</span>
        <span>Browser extension + chatbot entry</span>
      </div>
      <div>Choose the interface that fits the job</div>
    </footer>
  </main>
</LightLayout>
